pros:
First, I feel respected during working at Nokia;
Second, Nokia always encourage people to make  changes to optimize their work;
Third, Nokia is a company that pay much attention on EDU and training

Great company in a beautiful city, the vision is to expand the human possibilities of the connected world. the company cares about customers and employees. you can balance between work and life when you enjoy it ;
many opportunity you can get and can show your performance in the stage and advantage in it.
also, it's a company with various cultures. you can meet lots of friends in nokia.

- flexibility;
- good work and life balance;
- abundance of own online trainings;
- good multinational environment, diverse background, respectful environment.

cons:
- matrix line management (you might never see your line manager in face);
- hard to get a promotion and even harder to get the job grade upgraded;
- bureaucracy (complicated and time-consuming procedures);
